Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces; place in a medium #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-15%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot.

Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

While potatoes cook, trim, peel, and quarter @carrots{6%ounce} lengthwise; slice crosswise into 1⁄4-inch-thick quarter-moons. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, carrots, shallot, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until veggies begin to soften and beef is browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. If veggies begin to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Carefully drain any excess grease from pan.

While beef mixture cooks, in a small #bowl{}, combine @tomato paste{1}, @beef stock concentrate{2}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, half the @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}, half the @garlic powder{2%teaspoon}, and 1⁄2 cup reserved potato cooking liquid.

> You'll use the rest of the garlic powder later. Ladle water directly from pot if potatoes are still cooking.

Stir tomato paste mixture into pan with beef mixture and bring to a boil. Cover and reduce to a low simmer; cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has thickened and beef is cooked through, ~{5-8%minutes}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Remove from heat.

Return pot with potatoes to medium-low heat. Add @butter{2%tablespoon}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed.

Season with salt and pepper.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Transfer beef filling to an 8-by-8-inch #baking dish{}. Top with an even layer of mashed potatoes, leaving a 1-inch gap around the edges of the dish. Evenly sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}.

Bake cottage pie on top rack until topping is golden and filling is bubbling, ~{10-12%minutes}. Let rest at least ~{5%minutes} before serving.

Wash and dry pan used for beef filling.

Once cottage pie has 5 minutes left, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for beef filling over medium-high heat. Add @peas{4%ounce}, remaining garlic powder, and a pinch of salt.

Cook, stirring constantly, until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide cottage pie and peas between #shallow bowls{} in separate sections. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.